defaultIn collaboration with colleagues, we identified 
defaultappendix
default tissue s
defaultamples
default that had been removed from some individuals who subsequently developed and died from vCJD, and found that the abnormal prion protein coul
defaultd accumulate in lymphoid follicles in the appendix
default before the onset of symptoms of vCJD
default (13,14)
default. This finding l
defaultead to the hypothesis that the prevalence
